===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|capitalis|capitālis|lang=la|of the head}}, in sense “head of [[cattle]]”, from {{term|caput||head|lang=la}} (English {{term|cap|lang=en}}). Use in trade and finance originated in Medieval economies when a common but expensive transaction involved trading heads of cattle.

Compare {{term|chattel|lang=en}} and {{term|kith and kine||all one’s possessions|lang=en}}, which also use “cow” to mean “property”.

